---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import EventsCalendars from '../../src/components/pdx/EventsCalendars.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="PDX Events"
  description="A curated Portland events calendar — things to do in Portland, OR including farmers markets, trivia nights, Pedalpalooza, and local staples. Updated regularly."
  pageClass="page-events"
  ogImage="/images/IMG_1945.jpg"
>
  <!-- Hero image -->
  <div class="w-full relative" style="height: 420px; overflow: hidden;">
    <img
      src="/images/IMG_1945.jpg"
      alt="Portland, Oregon skyline and cityscape"
      class="w-full h-full object-cover"
      loading="eager"
    />
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-t from-black/50 to-transparent flex items-end">
      <div class="px-6 pb-8 max-w-5xl mx-auto w-full">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-semibold text-white drop-shadow" style="font-family: var(--font-serif)">Portland Events</h1>
        <p class="text-white/80 text-lg mt-2 max-w-xl drop-shadow">Curated calendars for things happening around Portland — events, markets, trivia, rides, and more.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <EventsCalendars />

  <!-- FAQ — gives AI search engines and Google text content to index -->
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 pb-16">
    <section class="bg-white rounded-2xl border border-stone-100 shadow-sm p-6">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-6" style="font-family: var(--font-serif)">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <dl class="space-y-6">

        <div>
          <dt class="font-semibold text-stone-800 mb-1">What's happening in Portland this weekend?</dt>
          <dd class="text-stone-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">The Portland Events calendar is updated regularly with festivals, markets, performances, and local happenings. For last-minute options, the Portland Events and Farmers Markets calendars are the best starting points — something is almost always going on.</dd>
        </div>

        <div>
          <dt class="font-semibold text-stone-800 mb-1">When do Portland farmers markets run?</dt>
          <dd class="text-stone-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">Portland farmers markets run nearly every day of the week across the metro area, from spring through fall. The PSU Saturday Market in the South Park Blocks is the largest, but neighborhood markets in Beaverton, Hillsboro, Lake Oswego, and beyond run throughout the week. The Farmers Markets calendar above shows them all.</dd>
        </div>

        <div>
          <dt class="font-semibold text-stone-800 mb-1">Where can I find trivia nights in Portland?</dt>
          <dd class="text-stone-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">Portland has a thriving pub quiz scene, with weekly trivia nights at bars and venues across N/NE, NW/SW, SE Portland, and surrounding areas. The Trivia Nights calendar shows them all in one view — you can toggle by neighborhood using the checkboxes in the embed. Spots fill up fast, so arrive early.</dd>
        </div>

        <div>
          <dt class="font-semibold text-stone-800 mb-1">What is Pedalpalooza?</dt>
          <dd class="text-stone-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">Pedalpalooza is Portland's annual celebration of cycling culture, organized by the Shift community. It features hundreds of themed bike rides over several weeks each summer. The calendar above tracks Shift bike events year-round — not just during Pedalpalooza season.</dd>
        </div>

        <div>
          <dt class="font-semibold text-stone-800 mb-1">Are these events free?</dt>
          <dd class="text-stone-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">Most events on these calendars are free or low-cost. Farmers markets are free to browse, trivia nights are typically free to play, and most Pedalpalooza and Shift rides are open to anyone with a bike. Paid events are noted on the individual calendar entries.</dd>
        </div>

      </dl>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
